Bha An Rathad Iarruinn Caledonian "An Calaidh", na rathad-iarruinn as motha an Albainn gu ruige 1923 nuair a chaidh e mar "constituent company" do an London Midland and Scottish Railway. 101 miltean 's an fhad, shine bun-loidhne a' Chalaidh bho Carlisle ( Far an do cheangail e ris an Rathad-Iarruinn "London and North Western") ri Ionad Meadhanach a' Ghlaschu. Bha fior branndair nan rathad-iaruinn an sheilbh a'chompanaidh seo, a chosnaich a' chuid bu mhor den tuarasdail aice bho trachdadh ghuail bho meinichean air feadh Srath Meadhanach na h-Alba. A dh'aindeoin sin, bha a phriomh gobhalach aig Tobar na Mathair, far an do dhealaich a rathad gu Obar-Dheathain. Thogta fo ainm "The Scottish Central Railway", fhosgladh an meur seo a chaidh tro Sruighlaidh, Pheart, Forfair agus Ceann Abair gu Sron na h-Aibhne agus Obar Dheathan cho trath ri 1848.
